## Layout
- `src/` - frontend code
- `api/` - backend functions/endpoints
- `auth/` - identity provider notes, scopes, redirect URIs
- `deploy/` - pointers to the IaC modules (deployment lives in `automation/iac/portal/` if that room exists)

## Rules
- Sign-in scoped to the intended audience. Outsiders rejected.
- Every state-changing action logged with the calling user's identity.
- Read-only by default. Destructive actions require explicit confirm.
- No secrets in frontend code. Backend pulls from a secret store via managed identity or equivalent.
- No tokens in localStorage. Use HTTP-only cookies or in-memory only.
- No custom auth. Use a vetted library for the identity provider.
- Frontend talks to backend through the API layer, not directly to lab/automation.

